":{"1342–":"1342–Deceased","1340–1407":"1340–1407","1397–1420":"1397–1420","1342–Female":"1342–Deceased","1420":"1420","1342":"1342","1397":"1397","1340":"1340","1407":"1407","Pembroke, Wales":"Pembrokeshire, Wales","Elmore Hall, Apsley Gyse, Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, England","Raglan, Monmouthshire, Wales":"Raglan, Monmouthshire, Wales","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Wogan","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Welsh, English, and Irish (Dublin): from the Old Welsh personal name <i>Guoccaun</i>, which derives from the ancestor of Modern Welsh <i>gogawn</i> ‘honour, glory’. In Middle Welsh it became <i>Gwogon</i> and <i>Gwogan</i> and was adopted as a surname by a south Pembrokeshire Anglo-Norman family in the normanized or Anglicized pronunciation <i>Wogan</i>. Compare   Cadogan  . In Ireland the name has been Gaelicized as <b>Úgán</b>.","History: A family of this name settled in County Kildare following the Anglo-Norman invasion of the 12th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Ogan","meanings":["Irish: of Welsh origin, a variant of   Wogan  , found Gaelicized as <b>Úgán</b>."]},{"name":"Vogan","meanings":["Irish: of Welsh origin, a variant of   Wogan  ."]},{"name":"Cadogan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Dermot.","Welsh (Pembrokeshire and Glamorgan) and Irish (of Welsh origin): from the Old Welsh personal name <i>Catgucaun</i>, <i>Catguocawn</i>, modernized as <i>Cadwgon</i>. It is composed of <i>cad</i> ‘battle’ + <i>gogawn</i> ‘honour, glory’. See also   Wogan  . The surname is stressed, like its Welsh original, on the penultimate syllable, hence its occasional development to   Duggan  .","Irish: from <b>Ó Ceadagáin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Ceadagán</i>’."]}]},{"name":"Katherine","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: Same as Catherine."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Katherine Wogan was born in 1342, in Pembrokeshire, Wales. She had at least 1 son with Anselem De Gyse. She died in Raglan, Monmouthshire, Wales."},"et":{"1342–":"1342–Surnud","1340–1407":"1340–1407","1397–1420":"1397–1420","1342–Female":"1342–Surnud","1420":"1420","1342":"1342","1397":"1397","1340":"1340","1407":"1407","Pembroke, Wales":"Pembrokeshire, Wales","Elmore Hall, Apsley Gyse, Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, England","Raglan, Monmouthshire, Wales":"Raglan, Monmouthshire, Wales"},"fi":{"1342–":"1342–Kuollut","1340–1407":"1340–1407","1397–1420":"1397–1420","1342–Female":"1342–Kuollut","1420":"1420","1342":"1342","1397":"1397","1340":"1340","1407":"1407","Pembroke, Wales":"Pembrokeshire, Wales","Elmore Hall, Apsley Gyse, Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, England","Raglan, Monmouthshire, Wales":"Raglan, Monmouthshire, Wales"},"fr":{"1342–":"1342–Décédée","1340–1407":"1340–1407","1397–1420":"1397–1420","1342–Female":"1342–Décédée","1420":"1420","1342":"1342","1397":"1397","1340":"1340","1407":"1407","Pembroke, Wales":"Pembrokeshire, Galles","Elmore Hall, Apsley Gyse, Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, Angleterre","Raglan, Monmouthshire, Wales":"Raglan, Monmouthshire, Galles","lifeSummary":"Katherine Wogan est née en 1342, à Pembrokeshire, Galles. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Anselem De Gyse. Elle est décédée à Raglan, Monmouthshire, Galles."},"de":{"1342–":"1342–Verstorben","1340–1407":"1340–1407","1397–1420":"1397–1420","1342–Female":"1342–Verstorben","1420":"1420","1342":"1342","1397":"1397","1340":"1340","1407":"1407","Pembroke, Wales":"Pembrokeshire, Wales","Elmore Hall, Apsley Gyse, Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, England","Raglan, Monmouthshire, Wales":"Raglan, Monmouthshire, Wales","lifeSummary":"Katherine Wogan wurde 1342 in Pembrokeshire, Wales geboren. Sie hatte mit Anselem De Gyse mindestens 1 Sohn. Sie starb in Raglan, Monmouthshire, Wales."},"ht":{"1342–":"1342–Desede","1340–1407":"1340–1407","1397–1420":"1397–1420","1342–Female":"1342–Desede","1420":"1420","1342":"1342","1397":"1397","1340":"1340","1407":"14